<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-19T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-19T11:00:00-05:00" n="784" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.822/73: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-19T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            19, 1919, 11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November 21, 3.20, p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>173. Referring to the Department’s October 16, 2 p.m. relative to
                                Roncador and other cays. Does the Department wish me to reply in
                                writing to the Foreign Office note of September 13th transmitted
                                with my despatch number 144 of September 17th as instructed in the
                                last paragraph of that telegram? My action has been confined to
                                verbal communications as the instructions received seemed intended
                                for that only.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>